{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Clause extractor identifies all key terms (parties, dates, obligations, penalties) present in the contract.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Failure boundary is semantic extraction quality from a real AI reviewer. In-process mocks can validate wiring but can miss real misses on legal phrasing and model variability.","test_description":"Run the real clause-extractor model on a curated set of real contract snippets with adjudicated key-term annotations, then assert required term categories are extracted with acceptable recall and correct span attribution.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.72,"Workflow":0.08}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Risk assessor flags problematic language under policy, including indirect/euphemistic phrasing.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Core correctness depends on model interpretation of nuanced language. Mocked classifier outputs would hide true false-negative risk on euphemisms.","test_description":"Call the real risk-assessor model with policy-configured prompts against a labeled corpus containing explicit and euphemistic risky clauses; assert high-risk examples are flagged and rationale/policy mapping is returned.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.04,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.83,"Workflow":0.07}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"Compliance checker determines whether contract meets regulatory requirements for configured jurisdiction.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"This is AI legal reasoning quality, not just deterministic rule wiring. Mocking would likely always pass and miss incorrect real judgments for jurisdiction-specific requirements.","test_description":"Invoke the real compliance-checker model for jurisdiction-specific test contracts with expert-labeled pass/fail outcomes and required citations; verify decision correctness and requirement-level coverage.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.75,"Workflow":0.1}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"Merge preserves conflicting assessments from different reviewers with attribution.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"Primary failure boundary is deterministic merge logic: conflict handling, attribution retention, and output schema. Real AI calls are unnecessary to trigger this class of bug.","test_description":"Feed the merge function structured reviewer outputs containing the same clause ID with conflicting labels and assert the merged report contains both assessments, reviewer attribution, and no overwrite.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.7,"Integration":0.22,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"End-to-end pipeline dispatches all three reviewers in parallel, collects results, and merges without losing findings for a real contract.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"This is a full agent pipeline with multiple real agentic steps plus orchestration/merge. Mocks can miss race, timeout, schema-drift, and result-loss failures that appear only with real concurrent reviewer outputs.","test_description":"Execute the production pipeline on a real contract using all three real reviewers concurrently; capture each reviewer’s raw output for that run and assert the final unified report preserves every finding (by clause/finding IDs) with reviewer attribution and no dropped sections.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.12,"Agentic":0.24,"Workflow":0.55}}]}
